-- Accel Hires Former Groupon President Solomon as Venture Partner
-- B y   A r i   L e v y
-- 2013-04-30T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-30/accel-hires-former-groupon-president-solomon-as-venture-partner.html
Accel Partners, the investment firm
that made a fortune from an early investment in Facebook Inc.,
said former Groupon Inc. president and operating chief  Rob Solomon  is joining as a venture partner.  Solomon will look to invest in early stage and maturing
technology companies, while working with startups on matters
including product management, business operations and mergers
and acquisitions, the Palo Alto, California-based firm said
today in a statement.  Solomon has a long history with Accel. He founded online
travel startup Sidestep Inc., which was acquired in 2007 by
Accel-backed  Kayak Software Corp. (KYAK)  Accel was an early investor in
Groupon, the daily-deal site where Solomon worked as a top
executive from 2010 to 2011. Heâ€™s also a director at High Gear
Media Inc., an Accel company.  Prior to joining Chicago-based Groupon, Solomon worked as a
venture partner at  Technology Crossover Ventures .  To contact the reporter on this story:
